SDMX XML Schemas: Rights and Provenance
========================================

This directory documents the official SDMX XML schemas that the sdmx-rs
workspace is modelled against. The repository tracks PINS and tooling only
(specs/sources.toml: per-edition commit + per-file sha256), never the schema
files themselves. The .xsd files are fetched on demand from upstream at the
pinned commit (see specs/README.md) and are not redistributed from this
repository.

Schemas
-------
The SDMX XML schemas are authored and published by the SDMX initiative and its
Technical Working Group (https://sdmx.org), sourced from the sdmx-twg/sdmx-ml
repository (https://github.com/sdmx-twg/sdmx-ml). Copyright in the schemas is
held by their respective owners. They are reproduced here only transiently, at
build time, for the purpose of modelling and validation; this project claims no
rights over them and grants none.

xml.xsd (W3C)
-------------
The xml.xsd shipped within each SDMX release tree is the W3C XML namespace
schema, copyright W3C (https://www.w3.org). It is fetched as part of the SDMX
release and is likewise not redistributed from this repository.

XSD contract fragments
----------------------
The XSD contract fragments under crates/sdmx-types/docs/xsd-fragments/ are
verbatim slices of the schemas above, generated at build time and used only in
the internal design_docs render. They carry the same rights as the schemas they
are sliced from and are likewise not redistributed: neither the published crate
nor docs.rs ever includes them.

